On branch master

No commits yet

Untracked files:
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
        git_file


*Git dosenot track those file which are in working space it track only the the file which are in staging are and local repository .

Sending the file from workimg area to staging area ---> git add <filename> or git add .

git add <file_name>   [or] git add . 


On branch master

No commits yet

Changes to be committed:
  (use "git rm --cached <file>..." to unstage)
        new file:   git_file

git commit -m "hint" 

git log 

git show <commit-id> 

"git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)	-> before git add <File> 

"git restore --staged <file>..." to unstage)				-> un stage 


connect/add Github(central repo)  to local repository , for the 1st time we need to add.

git remote add origin https://github.com/Kavithamane/central-repo.git

or create a new repository on the command line

echo "# demo" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/Kavithamane/demo.git
git push -u origin main

or push an existing repository from the command line

git remote add origin https://github.com/Kavithamane/demo.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

